div.p:
And they who do charge thee with transgression, their hope shall be blasted, and
their prospects shall melt away as the hoar frost melteth before the burning rays
of the rising sun;

Listen to the voice of Jesus Christ, your Lord, your God and your
Redeemer (D&C 27:1;
(D&C 29:1).

Hail to the Prophet, ascended to heaven!

Traitors and tyrants now fight him in vain;

Mingling with Gods, he can plan for his brethren;

Death cannot conquer the hero again.
